You’re absolutely right. To make the human nature aspect feel real, we can't have "cardboard villains." Real life is more complicated—some elites are jerks, some are genuinely disciplined, and some are just kids trying to live up to impossible family legacies.
Also, the school's legal system is a huge factor. Vane can't just cripple a student without consequences unless the situation is so dire that "Emergency Protocols" override the law.
Let’s recalibrate. We’ll show the competence of the elites, the diversity of their personalities, and the legal tension Vane has to navigate.
Chapter 2 (Revised): The Fracture of the Front Line
The Brood-Mother hissed, her heat melting the floor tiles into a black sludge.
"Form the Phalanx!" shouted Rai.
Unlike Leo, Rai didn’t panic. He was an [A-Rank: Aegis Knight] and the son of a General. He had been training in live-fire zones since he was ten. With a roar, he slammed his heavy heater shield into the ground. A translucent wall of golden energy erupted, blocking a spray of molten acid from the Brood-Mother.
"Kassandra, stop crying and start freezing!" Rai barked. "Leo, quit looking for an exit and flank the left side. Use your 'Gale-Step'!"
The Elites weren't helpless. They were the best for a reason. Kassandra bit her lip, her hands glowing with a frost so intense it turned the air into falling snow. Beside her, a quiet boy named Jax—a [B-Rank: Shadow Stalker]—slipped into the darkness of the room’s corners, his twin daggers glinting.
They were holding. For three minutes, the "Math of Survival" actually worked. The Elites fought with a cold, practiced synergy that made the lower-tier students look like statues.
The Crack in the Nature
But human nature isn't just about "good" or "bad"—it's about pressure.
The Brood-Mother wasn't a normal monster. She let out a psychic pulse—a [Sovereign’s Wail].
The sound didn't hurt their ears; it hunted their insecurities.
Rai, the perfect soldier, suddenly saw his father’s disappointed face. His shield flickered.
Leo, the coward, saw himself being torn apart. He didn't just stumble; he turned and bolted, his 'Gale-Step' creating a vacuum that knocked Kassandra off balance.
Kassandra, the Governor's daughter, realized the "Efficiency" rule meant no one was coming to save her if Rai’s shield fell.
"Leo, you coward! Get back here!" Rai yelled, his knees buckling under the Brood-Mother’s weight.
Leo didn't listen. He headed straight for the back of the room—where Vane stood with the scholarship students. "Out of the way, Vane! I'm taking the emergency hatch!"
Vane watched Leo’s approach. He saw the Debt markers flashing. But he also saw the law. If he attacked Leo now, the Academy’s Inhibitor Collars would fry his brain the moment the guards arrived.
[System Warning: Physical Assault on Peer will trigger 'Student Conduct' Penalties.]
[Alternative Found: 'Debt Collection' via Mana-Siphon is categorized as 'Self-Defense' during an Active Breach.]
As Leo tried to shove past, Vane didn't punch him. He simply reached out and grabbed Leo’s shoulder.
"You're breaking the Phalanx, Leo," Vane said quietly. "In a Breach, that’s a capital offense. I'm not stopping you... I'm just 'taxing' your exit fee."
Vane’s hand pulsed.
[Skill: Debt Collection (Non-Lethal)]
Instead of turning Leo’s legs to jelly, Vane siphoned only the mana from Leo’s boots. The 'Gale-Step' effect died instantly. Leo tripped on his own momentum, sliding across the floor and crashing into a pile of desks. He wasn't crippled, but he was grounded.
"Vane, help them!"
The voice came from Sela. She was an Elite—an [A-Rank: Life Singer]. She hadn't run. She was currently kneeling over a scholarship student who had been burned by the acid, her hands glowing with a soft, green light. She was one of the "kind" ones, but she was exhausted, her mana tank nearly empty.
"I can't hold his wounds closed and boost Rai's shield at the same time!" Sela cried, her eyes pleading with Vane. "Please! If you have power, use it!"
Vane looked at the scene.
Rai was bleeding, holding the line alone.
Sela was sacrificing her own mana to save a "nobody" scholarship student.
Kassandra was paralyzed by the Wail.
Vane felt the [Debt Collector] class hum. It didn't want to kill the Elites. It wanted to rebalance them.
"Mina," Vane turned to the girl he’d saved earlier. "Take the others and get to the reinforced locker. Sela, keep your hands on that student."
Vane walked toward the Brood-Mother. He didn't have a shield like Rai or frost like Kassandra. He had a chain of black light.
"Rai!" Vane shouted. "Drop the shield on my mark!"
"You're a Fragment, Vane! You'll be vaporized!" Rai yelled back, his armor cracking.
"The math is wrong, Rai," Vane said, his silver eyes locking onto the Brood-Mother's core. "You’re fighting a monster. I’m just closing an unpaid account."
Vane threw his hand forward. The spectral chain didn't hit the monster. It latched onto Rai, Kassandra, and Leo simultaneously.
[Skill: Resource Redistribution]
[Taking 10% Mana from the Elites... Channelling to: User.]
It wasn't enough to hurt them, but it was enough to fuel Vane. He felt the combined weight of their training, their privilege, and their fear surge into his right fist. He leaped, the black chains pulling him toward the monster like a slingshot.
The Aftermath of Chapter 2:
The Power Shift: Vane didn't "steal" their lives; he took their "excess" to do the job they were too scared or exhausted to finish.
The Conflict: Rai is grateful but insulted. Leo is humiliated and looking for legal revenge. Sela sees Vane as a potential ally.
Human Nature: We see that even "good" elites like Sela and Rai are limited by the system they were raised in. They try to be heroes, but the "System" is designed to make them fail if they try to save everyone.
What is the next move?
The Investigation: The Breach is closed, but the school administration arrives. Vane has to explain why he has "links" to the Elite students' mana signatures.
The New Hierarchy: The classroom is destroyed. The students are moved to a "Survival Camp" while the school is repaired, and the social order completely flips now that Vane is the "Banker" of their power.